<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-07-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="419" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                            <head><seg type="margin">[102]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Pierrepont</persName>, district attorney, to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Fish</persName>, Secretary of
                                    State.</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-07-15"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 15, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p rend="flushleft">Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamilton Fish</hi>:</p>
                            <p>The commission of the President and your orders have been received.
                                Will be promptly executed. Present difficulty, as marshal advised,
                                is in finding the ship. Every means will be taken.</p>
                            <p>Yours, respectfully,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>EDWARDS PIERREPONT,<lb/><hi rend="italic">United
                                        States-Attorney.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>